`,e.exports.jsx(t.p,{children:"Now, lets make a new cone, and lets place it to the left of the sphere. There is no correct way to do this, but a useful trick is to make this group a child of the group which contains the sphere already. This way, we can use the sphere's position as a reference point for the cone. Let's create a new group as a child of the group containing the sphere:"}),`
